03/11/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament approved an arbitration agreement Monday (November 2nd) aimed at resolving the long-standing border dispute with Slovenia.
The document was approved by a vote of 80-8, with 45 lawmakers abstaining.
The parliamentary approval gives the government the green light to sign the agreement.
Lawmakers also supported a unilateral statement that clarifies the agreement does not pre-judge the outcome of international arbitration.
(HRT, Javno, HINA, Index, NovaTV - 02/11/09)
